usage: git publish [<options>]

Publish last versions of submodules and dev branch of startup module.

    -h|--help               display help
    -t|--vtable             force vtable creation when startup module is a composite submodule
                            (default is to create a vtable only when the startup module is a bundle)
    -u|--reuse              reuse most recent vtag of startup module (move it to current branch tip)
    -j<n>                   number of submodules published in parallel (default to 16)
    --alpha                 publish branch of startup module as alpha version
    --beta                  publish branch of startup module as beta version
    --rc                    publish branch of startup module as RC version
    --rtm                   publish branch of startup module as RTM version (remove pre-release version)
    --dev                   publish dev branches of submodules (default to last version)
    --prod                  try attach to prod branch (default to dev branch) after publish
    .                       do not publish submodules

example:
    git publish             # publish last version of submodules and dev branch of startup module
                            # try to attach to dev branches of submodules
                            # create a vtable if the startup module is a bundle
    git publish --dev       # publish dev branch of all modules
    git publish --prod      # publish last version of submodules and prod branch of startup module
                            # try to attach to prod branches of all modules
    git publish --alpha     # publish last version of submodules and dev branch of startup module as alpha version
    git publish --reuse     # publish last version of submodules and reuse most recent vtag of startup module
    git publish --vtable    # create a vtable when publishing a composite submodule even if it's not a bundle
    git publish .           # publish current module only
